
Conducted a quantitative risk assessment of Canada Lifes acquisition of Santé Circle Health by analyzing the three highest-priority risks identified during the qualitative assessment phase:

R-003: Cross-Selling Revenue Synergy Shortfall
R-010: Personal Health Information (PHI) Data Breach
R-013:Legacy System Incompatibility

The aim was to convert subjective risk ratings into measurable, data-driven estimates using risk modeling, Monte Carlo simulation, machine learning techniques, and Indicators & Warnings (I&W) monitoring frameworks.

Key Methodologies

Monte Carlo Simulation

Used simulations to model uncertainty and estimate potential financial impacts for:

* Revenue synergy achievement
* System integration downtime costs

Generated probability distributions, expected outcomes, and P10/P90 scenarios for executive decision making.

Expected Monetary Value (EMV) Analysis

Calculated financial exposure for cybersecurity and data breach risks using:
Industry breach probability benchmarks
Healthcare breach cost estimate
Regulatory penalty exposure

Machine Learning Risk Modeling

Applied predictive models to identify leading indicators of risk:

Random Forest Classification

PHI breach risk prediction
Security control weakness identification

Gradient Boosting

system integration failure prediction
Technical incompatibility assessment

